[49m[38;5;10m+      1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 6.7: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the clinical trial patient matching pipeline from Recipe 6.7. It demonstrates the multi-stage filtering approach (structured pre-screen, NLP deep screen, scoring) using synthetic data and boto3 calls. It is not production-ready. Real trial matching requires validated criteria parsers, IRB-approved workflows, and integration with your EHR. Think of this as the sketch on the whiteboard, not the blueprint you'd hand to a contractor.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few standard libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2` (Comprehend Medical)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `athena:StartQueryExecution`, `athena:GetQueryExecution`, `athena:GetQueryResults`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:Query`
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before the logic, here's the configuration that drives the matching pipeline. Trial criteria definitions, scoring weights, and thresholds all live here so they're easy to find and adjust per trial.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. Never log PHI field values (patient names, MRNs, etc.).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Retry config for AWS API calls. Adaptive mode handles throttling gracefully.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # AWS clients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m comprehend_medical = boto3.client("comprehendmedical", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m athena_client = boto3.client("athena", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Configuration
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m RESULTS_BUCKET = "trial-matching-results"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ATHENA_OUTPUT = "s3://trial-matching-results/athena-output/"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ATHENA_DATABASE = "patient_data_lake"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CANDIDATES_TABLE = "trial-candidates"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Confidence threshold for NLP-based criterion evaluation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Below this, we mark the criterion as UNCERTAIN rather than PASS/FAIL.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NLP_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.75
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Scoring weights by criterion type. Structured criteria get higher weight
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # because they're deterministic. NLP criteria get lower weight because
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # they carry inherent uncertainty.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SCORING_WEIGHTS = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "STRUCTURED": 1.0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "UNSTRUCTURED": 0.8,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "BOTH": 0.9,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Synthetic Trial Criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Real trial criteria come from ClinicalTrials.gov. For this example, we define a simplified set of criteria for a fictional GLP-1 combination therapy trial. Each criterion specifies what data source it needs and how to evaluate it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
